Deutsche Bank Says ‘Don’t Panic’ on Brazil Banks Asset Quality

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-05-20T15:14:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/deutsche-bank-says-don-t-panic-on-brazil-banks-asset-quality.html
Brazilian banks’ deteriorating asset
quality is already reflected in share-price declines and the
industry may outperform when inflation expectations improve,
Deutsche Bank AG said.  Brazilian financial stocks’ “steep discount” to Latin
American peers is “unjustified,” Mario Pierry, an analyst at
Deutsche Bank, wrote in a note to clients.  “Don’t panic over asset quality,” Pierry said in the
note.  To contact the reporter on this story:
